    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Neill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1890</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Hicks’s No. 56, of December 20,
                    1889, and 91, of February 21, last, both relating to the claim of the
                    Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon against the Government of Peru, you are
                    instructed to ask the foreign office whether the treasury department has made
                    any report to it in regard to the claim; and if not, to urge that action may be
                    taken. Mr. Hicks stated that the justice of the claim was admitted by the
                    officials of the foreign office.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
